From: Codex <codex@local>
Subject: [PATCH] lib80211: instantiate ccm(aes) before atomic transmit

The staging r8188eu driver can allocate its lib80211 CCMP context from a
softirq transmit path.  The first ccm(aes) allocation may invoke cryptomgr
and request_module(), which sleeps and crashes the kernel in atomic context.
Warm the composed transform during module initialization, where sleeping is
allowed, before registering the CCMP operations with lib80211.
---
 net/wireless/lib80211_crypt_ccmp.c | 17 +++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 17 insertions(+)

diff --git a/net/wireless/lib80211_crypt_ccmp.c b/net/wireless/lib80211_crypt_ccmp.c
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/net/wireless/lib80211_crypt_ccmp.c
+++ b/net/wireless/lib80211_crypt_ccmp.c
@@ -437,2 +437,19 @@ static struct lib80211_crypto_ops lib80211_crypt_ccmp = {
 static int __init lib80211_crypto_ccmp_init(void)
 {
+	struct crypto_aead *tfm;
+	int ret;
+
+	/*
+	 * r8188eu can create a CCMP key while transmitting from softirq.
+	 * Instantiate ccm(aes) here, in process context, so cryptomgr never
+	 * has to invoke request_module() from that atomic transmit path.
+	 */
+	tfm = crypto_alloc_aead("ccm(aes)", 0, CRYPTO_ALG_ASYNC);
+	if (IS_ERR(tfm)) {
+		ret = PTR_ERR(tfm);
+		pr_err("lib80211_crypt_ccmp: failed to warm up ccm(aes): %d\n",
+		       ret);
+		return ret;
+	}
+	crypto_free_aead(tfm);
+
